%% Branch-level state machine.
%% Clarifies the lifecycle of a single branch-level pair and the difference between passing once and owning.
stateDiagram-v2
direction LR

[*] --> Unopened

Unopened --> Training: prerequisites owned and branch opened
Training --> TestReady: two recent clean practice sessions
TestReady --> Training: readiness expires or preparation incomplete
TestReady --> PassedOnce: formal test passed once
TestReady --> Training: test failed and response prescribed
PassedOnce --> Stabilizing: enter stabilization phase
Stabilizing --> Owned: two additional clean passes within 14 days
Stabilizing --> Training: stabilization fail classified
Owned --> Maintenance: lower-volume checks assigned
Maintenance --> Owned: maintenance pass current
Maintenance --> Decayed: two failed checks or prerequisite maintenance failure
Decayed --> Training: restore prerequisite at lower load
Decayed --> Maintenance: last owned standard plus lower-load transfer check passed
Owned --> Training: next level unlocks if global balance allows
Maintenance --> Training: global review opens next demand

Training --> Training: practice, load, regression, or recovery
Owned --> Owned: global review passes
Maintenance --> Maintenance: check not yet due

note right of TestReady
  Test readiness requires owned prerequisites,
  clean recent practice, current maintenance,
  a stated standard, and a named honesty constraint.
end note

note right of PassedOnce
  Passed once is not ownership.
  The next level remains locked.
end note

note right of Owned
  Ownership requires repeatability across days,
  at least one pass after adjacent work or distraction,
  and no standard changes.
end note

note right of Decayed
  Decay caps dependent advancement until restoration.
end note
